        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1000884610" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9798862573170129287">A fine ending to the trilogy. <br/><br/>I think the book drags a lot and it could have been a lot shorter. The moral pangs the Reverend faces are totally useless here. He had two books to come to terms with the Hunter and his ways. I don&apos;t need to read again and again about his spiritual agony.<br/><br/>Generally, I liked the ending and I believe that the author resolved everything nicely. I can&apos;t help but feel that the world emerging after that is not one I would like as much. Magic dies and the world becomes ordi</span>
  <span id="freeText9798862573170129287" style="display:none">A fine ending to the trilogy. <br /><br />I think the book drags a lot and it could have been a lot shorter. The moral pangs the Reverend faces are totally useless here. He had two books to come to terms with the Hunter and his ways. I don't need to read again and again about his spiritual agony.<br /><br />Generally, I liked the ending and I believe that the author resolved everything nicely. I can't help but feel that the world emerging after that is not one I would like as much. Magic dies and the world becomes ordinary. I prefered it when the fae created monsters. At least, it was full of potential.<br /><br />It is a good series. I recommend it to anyone wanting to read something different, with a unique magic system. It makes you think about religion, good and evil, revenge and second chances. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9798862573170129287" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


